The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for computing sequences of contractions and removals, which are topics that are typically studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses 3-connectivity and 3-edge-connectivity tests, which are important topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents algorithms with improved running times, which is a topic that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
